Thank you for downloading the SpeechBuilder starter pack! The archive
that you have downloaded should include four files:

README			This file
flights.xml		XML definition of flights domain
flights.cgi		CGI back-end for flights domain (in PERL)
SpeechBuilder.pm	SpeechBuilder support library

Here is a step-by step procedure to get your first SpeechBuilder
domain up and running:

1. Copy the flights.cgi script to a directory on your web server that
   is configured to run CGI scripts. Test it out with a web browser.
2. Look at the flights.xml file and edit the URL to point to wherever
   your back-end script from step 1 is accessible.
3. Go to the SpeechBuilder page at
   http://speech.lcs.mit.edu/SpeechBuilder/SpeechBuilder.cgi .
4. When prompted for User Name and Password, click "Cancel".
5. You will be taken to the login denied page. Click on the "click
   here to register" link.
6. Enter your information and click on Register to set up your
   account.
7. Click on the "click here" link to go to the sytem.
8. Enter your login information and click "ok".
9. Type "flights" in the "Pick a domain name" window and click
   "create".
10.You will be taken to the main SpeechBuilder editing page. Scroll
   down to the bottom to see the XML uploading tool. Click "Browse"
   and find the "flights.xml" file on your hard drive. Click "Open"
   and click on "Upload XML" in the browser.
11.Click on the "Refresh" button once your XML file is uploaded.
12.You will be at the domain editing screen. Click "Build" at the
   bottom of the page to build your application.
13.Click "Start" to get your domain running.
14.You should be all set! Call your domain and talk to it!
